# Git Workflow

## Branching

Branch from `main`. Direct pushes to `main` are forbidden.

| Prefix | Use for | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `feat/` | new features | `feat/comment-moderation` |
| `fix/` | bug fixes | `fix/login-redirect-loop` |
| `chore/` | maintenance | `chore/update-deps` |
| `docs/` | docs only | `docs/api-reference` |

Keep branches focused and rebased onto latest `main` before requesting review.

## Conventional commits

```
<type>: <short summary, <=72 chars>

[optional body]

[optional footer, e.g. Closes #42]
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`, `refactor`, `style`, `perf`, `ci`.

Examples:

```
feat: [US-46] - open-source community files
fix: correct token expiry calculation in auth refresh
docs: update API route documentation
```

## Pull requests

- Open a **draft PR early** to share approach.
- Fill out the PR template: summary, related issues, test plan, screenshots for UI changes.
- All CI jobs must pass: `lint`, `typecheck`, `test-unit`, `test-integ`, `test-e2e`, `test-a11y`, `build`, `ci-success`.
- Squash-merge is preferred. Delete the branch after merge.

## PR checklist (must be true before "ready for review")

- Tests added/updated for changed behavior.
- TypeScript types are correct (no unjustified `any`).
- No new ESLint errors or warnings.
- Migrations use `IF NOT EXISTS` (see database rule).
- New API routes have rate limit, security headers, auth/RBAC where applicable.
- WCAG 2.1 AA preserved on UI changes.
